<h1>Problem 1102 - 2015 India TST, Day 1, P1 of 3, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>Let \(ABCD\) be a convex quadrilateral and let the diagonals \(AC\) and \(BD\) intersect at \(O\). Let \(I_1, I_2, I_3, I_4\) be respectively the incentres of triangles \(AOB, BOC, COD, DOA\). Let \(J_1, J_2, J_3, J_4\) be respectively the excentres of triangles \(AOB, BOC, COD, DOA\) opposite \(O\). Show that \(I_1, I_2, I_3, I_4\) lie on a circle if and only if \(J_1, J_2, J_3, J_4\) lie on a circle.</p>
